  "description": "Removal of pre-cast concrete coping stones and replacement (same material) to provide a sufficient drip detail to the entire length of both parapet walls; removal of felt patch repair, inspection of brickwork below and repair where necessary; gentle removal of the render to the parapet walls and chimney stacks using a hammer and bolster with care to ensure the brickwork is unaffected when removing the render and removal by hand in small sections of the render  in order to ensure the integrity of the brickwork; cleaning of the brickwork using water and a wire brush, removing any grime or soot, inspection of the brickwor and repairs to be carried out as necessary; if the brickwork is unaffected continue removal of the render in the same fashion; damaged brickwork to be cut out as necessary, either side of the fracture, one face only, new bricks to be stitched in, bed and pointed with a lime based mortar 1:3 (hydraulic lime: sharp sand); repointing where necessary by raking out existing joints of brickwork minimum 12mm deep, repointing in mortar and removal of spoil; renewal of lead flashing. Internally, the existing plaster is to be stripped from all surfaces affected by water penetration with application of a non-hydraulic lime based plaster (of a mix of 3 parts sharp well graded sand, 1 part non hydraulic lime putty, goat hair- 2kg per tonne of plaster) prior to decoration.",
